text: Hello! Let’s say I have an extra cloned version of a theme. If I try to delete that extra clone and all the modules inside its folder I get a warning about live dependencies with many dependencies. Am I safe to delete this cloned version that I don’t use or should I do this another way? I did not use that extra clone to build any pages. It was just an experiment. Thanks in advance!

I've run into this a lot lately as I've been doing a lot of experimenting so I'm going to give you suggestions from my experience. Click on the view dependencies and see what they are. Are they just testing pages? This can trigger the dependencies. Delete them and then see if dependencies are still there if so review them.
